open aws ec2
search for vpc
click on create vpc
vpc only
give name
cidr=10.0.0.0/16
create vpc

click on internet gateway
create new gateway
give name
click on create

go back to internet gateway
select the internet gateway created
click on actions
attach to vpc
select vpc name
click on attach internet gateway

two subnets will be created; one will be public while the other one will be private

click on subnet
create key
select vpc created
give vpc name
put ipv4 as 10.0.0.0/24
click create subnet
two different zone
one is public the other one is public; give name as such

select the correct vpc by name
ipv4 cidr = 10.0.0.0/16
ipv4 subnet cidr = 10.0.0.0/24 (public)
ipv4 subnet cidr = 10.0.1.0/24 (private)
click create subnet

goto route table
create two route table : one for public the other for private
give appropiate name
select vpc
create route table

for the public one:
  edit route
  add route
  add 0.0.0.0/0
  add gateway : internet gateway
  igw select full name
  save changes

to differentiate between the public and private route table, 
select the route table -> subnet association -> edit subnet association -> select the correct association according to public and private -> save changes

goto ec2
launch two instances with the same secuirity group and key; but different region ; two instances : one public, the other one private
in the public instance 
  choose auto assign public ip = enable
  fot the private one = disable
create instance
8gb and gp2
launch instance

first connect the enabled instance in the terminal (public  and private in the same terminal)

